Johnson Controls Chairman Barth to retire


July 26, 2007 @ 4:37 pm


Comments


Email



Brent Snavely

Crain's Detroit Business






		SHARE 


Facebook 
Twitter 
LinkedIn 
Google+ 




0
Shares
















Johnson Controls
John Barth
People
United States


















John Barth








Send us a Letter
Have an opinion about this story? Click here to submit a Letter to the Editor, and we may publish it in print.


DETROIT -- Johnson Controls Inc. said today that Chairman and CEO John Barth will retire Dec. 31 but remain a member of the company�s board.The company said Stephen Roell, the company�s executive vice president and vice chairman, has been elected chairman and CEO. Roell will become CEO on Oct. 1 and will become chairman on Jan. 1.Johnson Controls� automotive division is based in Plymouth, Mich. It ranks No. 5 on the Automotive News list of top 100 global original equipment suppliers with global original equipment sales of $19.50 billion in the 2006 fiscal year.Barth became CEO of Johnson Controls in 2002, when the company had annual sales of about $20 billion. Johnson Controls expects to end 2007 with sales of more than $34.5 billion and a track record of 17 consecutive years of earnings increases.You may e-mail Brent Snavely at bsnavely@crain.com



You can reach Brent Snavely at bsnavely@crain.com 



Tags:
Johnson Controls
John Barth
People
United States


